column5: very nice, congrats!
Great looking boat Ryan I just bought one about the same last year it has been a amazing boat to me and the family what year is yours? With that 115 how fast do you get out of it?
Congrats very nice boat indeed.
If you're goal of the post was to make people jealous, you've succeeded.... lol  Awesome boat, looks great for fishing & family time.  Cheers

Finally sort of figured out how to post a pic again. Here are a few pics of my new (to me ) Starcraft 17ft. Fishmaster. This replaces my 14 ft. tinner with a 15 hp. Johnson. Thanks to FISHERMAN for the advice on adding plug for trolling motor and a battery relay. I am looking forward to many years on this baby!!
Congrats Ryan !!
great looking boat!  That'll be years of fun on the water.
Great thing is that even my wife likes it!!!
